Document: WebRTCMultiplayerPeer
Path: godot/classes/class_webrtcmultiplayerpeer.rst
Summary: Provides a multiplayer peer implementation using WebRTC.

WebRTCMultiplayerPeer is a multiplayer peer implementation that uses WebRTC for peer-to-peer communication. It allows for establishing connections between multiple peers and sending data reliably or unreliably. This class is useful for creating real-time multiplayer games or applications that require direct peer-to-peer communication.

Inherits: MultiplayerPeer < RefCounted
