Document: WebRTCMultiplayerPeer
Path: godot/classes/class_webrtcmultiplayerpeer.rst
Summary: This class constructs a full mesh of WebRTCPeerConnection objects for use with MultiplayerAPI.

Inherits: MultiplayerPeer < PacketPeerExtension < PacketPeer < RefCounted

This class constructs a full mesh of WebRTCPeerConnection (one connection for each peer) that can be used as a MultiplayerAPI.multiplayer_peer.

You can add each WebRTCPeerConnection via add_peer() or remove them via remove_peer(). Peers must be added in WebRTCPeerConnection.STATE_NEW state to allow it to create the appropriate channels. This class will not create offers nor set descriptions, it will only poll them, and notify connections and disconnections.

When creating the peer via create_client() or create_server() the MultiplayerPeer.is_server_relay_supported() method will return true enabling peer exchange and packet relaying when supported by the MultiplayerAPI implementation.

Note: When exporting to Android, make sure to enable the INTERNET permission in the Android export preset before exporting the project or using one-click deploy. Otherwise, network communication of any kind will be blocked by Android.
---CHUNK---
Document: WebRTCMultiplayerPeer
Path: godot/classes/class_webrtcmultiplayerpeer.rst
Summary: Provides methods for managing WebRTC peers in a multiplayer setup, including creating client/server connections, adding/removing peers, and retrieving peer information.

Method: add_peer(peer: WebRTCPeerConnection, peer_id: int, unreliable_lifetime: int = 1) → Error
Adds a new peer to the mesh with the given peer_id. The WebRTCPeerConnection must be in the STATE_NEW state. Three channels will be created: reliable, unreliable, and ordered. The unreliable_lifetime parameter is used for the "maxPacketLifetime" option when creating unreliable and ordered channels.

Method: create_client(peer_id: int, channels_config: Array = []) → Error
Initializes the multiplayer peer as a client with the specified peer_id (must be between 2 and 2147483647). This mode enables server relay support for peer exchange and packet relaying. Optionally, a channels_config array of TransferMode can be provided to create extra channels.

Method: create_mesh(peer_id: int, channels_config: Array = []) → Error
Initializes the multiplayer peer as a mesh (all peers connect to each other) with the given peer_id (must be between 1 and 2147483647).

Method: create_server(channels_config: Array = []) → Error
Initializes the multiplayer peer as a server with a unique ID of 1. This mode enables server relay support for peer exchange and packet relaying. Optionally, a channels_config array of TransferMode can be provided to create extra channels.

Method: get_peer(peer_id: int) → Dictionary
Returns a dictionary representation of the peer with the given peer_id. The dictionary contains "connection" (the WebRTCPeerConnection), "channels" (an array of three WebRTCDataChannel objects), and "connected" (a boolean indicating if the peer connection is currently active).

Method: get_peers() → Dictionary
Returns a dictionary where keys are peer IDs and values are the peer representations as returned by get_peer().

Method: has_peer(peer_id: int) → bool
Returns true if the given peer_id exists in the peers map, regardless of whether it is currently connected.

Method: remove_peer(peer_id: int) → void
Removes the peer with the specified peer_id from the mesh. If the peer was connected, this will emit the peer_disconnected signal.